<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 10 SPEED AND 15 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT, RTO, AND RTX
        SERIES - REASSEMBLE
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc id="hl1301504" svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="4">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With the gear shift lever housing secured in a vise, install the spade pin in the bore
                    of the housing tower (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13015c8">Figure 128</hotlnk>). If previously removed, install the O-ring in the
                    tower groove.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13015c8" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13015c8" filename="../figg13/G13015C8.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 128. Install Spade Pin in Housing Tower Bore</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the gear shift lever in the housing with the spade pin in the lever ball slot
                    and install the tension spring washer over the ball, dished-side up (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13015c9">Figure 129</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13015c9" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13015c9" filename="../figg13/G13015C9.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 129. Install Tension Spring Washer Over Ball</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the tension spring under the lugs in the housing,
                    <emph type="bold">seating one coil at a time</emph>
                    (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13015d0">Figure 130</hotlnk>). Use of a spring driving tool is recommended.
                </para>
                <figure id="f13015d0" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13015d0" filename="../figg13/G13015D0.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 130. Install Tension Spring Under Housing Lugs</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the assembly from the vise and install the rubber boot over the gear shift lever
                    and against the housing (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f13015d1">Figure 131</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f13015d1" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g13015d1" filename="../figg13/G13015D1.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 131. Install Rubber Boot Over Gear Shift Lever</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
